Description: At Gydem, our goal is to help you skip the tourist traps and do what the locals do!
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: With a passion for travel and exploration of new environments, “CitiGyde” was founded in early 2015. The company’s goal is to improve the travel experience for tourists all over the world.  Gydem is a mobile application that matches independent tourists with local inhabitants of a destination city. Our application uses geo-mapping and proximity matching in concurrence with a social rating system in order to provide the most convenient tour services available. Users will have the option to book services with priority given to time sensitivity or quality, giving them exactly what they want, exactly when they want it. Unlike traditional tour guide organizations, anyone will be able to sign up to be a local tour guide with the Gydem Application. Each tour guide will operate independently with no direction coming from the parent company. Decisions for tours will be made on the local’s knowledge, the traveler’s interests, and the availability of events/services at the time of operation. Charging an hourly rate for their service, the tour guides will have travelers pay for the tour through our application. Once we [the application developers] take a percentage of the revenue made from the sale, the remaining sum of money will be delivered to the tour guide as payment for their service. While there has been a dramatic rise in the number of “on-demand, geo-centric” services in a wide variety of neighboring industries, this particular phenomenon has yet to reach main stream status within the travel/hospitality industry. There are a number of applications that try to deliver guided tours within specified locations but very few take advantage of the person-to-person, local-on-tourist environment that can be created with modern technology. By offering distinct and unique tours that provide insider-access to the travel destinations, Gydem sets itself up as a strong player within the travel industry.

Description: Smart City, Transportation, Energy & Mobility IoT solutions to create the smart, liveable and sustainable cities of the future
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: We are a Smart City Solutions-as-a-Service company helping local governments and city operators use technology to connect business verticals through our Smart City Platform (i.e. street lighting, mobility, waste management, mobility, environment) creating horizontal synergies towards maximising efficiency, reducing costs and increasing sustainability. Our revenue model is based on selling / leasing the in-house developed technology and then charging a subscription fee for using the platform services (analytics, reports, visualisations etc.) The problem we are solving is reducing the operational costs for municipalities and city operators. The costs we are cutting are caused by : · high energy consumption with traditional street lighting · large amounts of water used for city gardens watering · unnecessary traffic caused by motorists searching for a parking space (about 30% of the traffic) · high operational costs (fuel, road-wear, trucks maintenance, employees) caused by un-optimised waste containers management Our main products are :  - a smart mobility station for multi-modal transportation and mobility-as-a-service, integrating various amazing features like : EV charging, e-bike charging, park meter, ride-sharing, car pooling , on-demand transportation, public transportation, journey planning , easy and secure Blockchain enabled payments and more. · smart fill-level sensors for waste containers · smart parking sensors for on-street / off-street parking monitoring, interconnected smart park-meters with integrated EV charging station and digital guidance systems to guide motorists to vacant parking spaces and curb traffic within the city · smart lighting systems (including environmental monitoring stations, alerting, traffic and public transportation reporting, soil monitoring etc) with event activated policies for high energy savings and efficient reporting · customised solutions for greenfield projects, including consulting during implementation.

MoolaHoop was developed to help narrow the gap in funding available to women entrepreneurs. Women-owned businesses represent almost 30% of new startups in the U.S., yet receive just 5% of all venture capital and 12% of all institutional debt. As a result, they are smaller from the onset and grow more slowly.  But what if that wasn’t the case? Then, women entrepreneurs could make their ideas grow faster, bigger and hit the ground running. MoolaHoop aims to help women fund the great ideas of tomorrow, today, by leveraging their social and professional networks. Description: Getting ringtones for your phone is a great way to interact with your favourite music and assert your personal style.

We've selected a large number of ringtones to help personalise your phone. In addition to ringtones, we've also found a great selection of wallpapers and screensavers to define your style. There are three types of ringtones: polyphonic ringtones; monophonic ringtones; and true tones. Monophonic ringtones consist of a series of different beeps made at different frequencies. They are compatible with today’s cell phones. Only one note can be played at a time. Polyphonic ringtones can consist of 16 sounds at once. The sounds create a melody that is harmonic. All new phones can use polyphonic ringtones. Companies that make cellphones that can use polyphonic ringtones include Motorola, Panasonic, Samsung, Sanyo, and others. There are many types available for download. MP3 Ringtones, or true tones, allow original instruments and voices. One can hear music of the past or current hits with true tones. Later phones are compatible with true tones. Whenever you get a call, you can hear your favorite song on your cell phone with a true tone.
